{"id":"32963143-6ed7-4d44-858f-31c7fb7ba948","level":3,"callsign":"Forlorn","name":"Kezil","player_name":"Kessel","status":"ACTIVE","dead":false,"text_appearance":"<p>WIP</p>","notes":"<p><br></p>","history":"<p><span style=\"background-color: oklab(0.498177 0.0184957 0.00168626 / 0.08);\">Kezil was born poor, down trotted on a Penal Colony of a moon within a planets orbit barren of life. The moon itself was a mining deposit and was your typical cut out of ruthless gangs and territory control of corporate powers. The colony itself was an industrial world. Mechanical factory’s, parts dispensary, and early to pre third war mechs put on full display and sold to rutheless mercenary groups within the outer limits of union space. The auction of bodies and frames put to full display, while family were torn apart at early ages. Kezil was an orphans by the laws of labor on the moon, pushed Kezil to a life of mech administration for mercenary groups that moved and weaved through the systems laws and dealings. Never enough to get out, never enough to risk his life to leave. Years passed on the penal colony; union vessels laid over the horizon in force driving most mercs and companies underground and as simple as it is, the people were free but lost in direction or purpose. Without overseers or leadership violent order of chaos and justice laid the foundations of a Wild West anarchy within the moon. Not many options were left for most, some opted to criminal and strife while some others chose to rise from their duty stations. Kezil was one such, he applied seeking Union assignment, thus he was plunged into the work forces of the union, not as a solider yet, but as a worker, and organizer amongst the administrative lower peons that laid at the bottom of the union food chain, rising up slowly as administrators saw potential in his leadership and charisma amongst the workers that usually aren’t so easily manipulated.</span></p>","quirks":[],"current_hp":8,"background":"Penal Colon